            "content": "# NATS Autoscaler Design\n\n**Date:** 2026-04-09\n**Status:** Approved\n**Scope:** Add autoscaler support to the NATS JetStream backend, following the cross-backend `AutoscalerBackend` trait pattern established by the RabbitMQ and SNS-SQS backends.\n\n## Overview\n\nRework `NatsConsumerGroup` to support dynamic scaling (scale_up/scale_down), add a `NatsConsumerGroupRegistry` for managing multiple groups, and implement `NatsAutoscalerBackend` that queries JetStream consumer info for metrics.\n\n## Components\n\n### 1. NatsConsumerGroup (rewrite)\n\nRework from a simple \"spawn and wait\" struct to a full scaling-capable consumer group matching the RabbitMQ `ConsumerGroup` pattern.\n\n```rust\ntype Spawner = Arc<dyn Fn(ConsumerOptions) -> JoinHandle<()> + Send + Sync>;\n\npub struct NatsConsumerGroup {\n    name: String,\n    queue: String,\n    config: NatsConsumerGroupConfig,\n    spawner: Spawner,\n    consumers: Vec<(CancellationToken, Arc<AtomicBool>, JoinHandle<()>)>,\n    group_token: CancellationToken,\n}\n```\n\n**Constructor:**\n```rust\npub fn new<T, H>(\n    name: impl Into<String>,\n    queue: impl Into<String>,\n    config: NatsConsumerGroupConfig,\n    client: NatsClient,\n    group_token: CancellationToken,\n    handler_factory: impl Fn() -> H + Send + Sync + 'static,\n) -> Self\nwhere\n    T: Topic + 'static,\n    H: MessageHandler<T> + Clone + 'static,\n```\n\nThe spawner closure captures `client` and `handler_factory`, producing a `JoinHandle` per consumer. Each consumer gets a child token of `group_token` and its own `Arc<AtomicBool>` processing flag.\n\n**Methods:**\n- `start(&mut self)` — spawns `min_consumers` consumers\n- `scale_up(&mut self) -> bool` — spawn one more, false if at max\n- `scale_down(&mut self) -> bool` — cancel last idle consumer, false if at min or all busy\n- `active_consumers(&self) -> usize`\n- `queue(&self) -> &str`\n- `config(&self) -> &NatsConsumerGroupConfig`\n- `shutdown(&mut self)` — cancel group token, await all tasks\n\n### 2. NatsConsumerGroupConfig (rework)\n\nRework to match the RabbitMQ builder pattern:\n\n```rust\npub struct NatsConsumerGroupConfig {\n    pub(crate) prefetch_count: u16,\n    pub(crate) min_consumers: u16,\n    pub(crate) max_consumers: u16,\n    pub(crate) max_retries: u32,\n    pub(crate) handler_timeout: Option<Duration>,\n    pub(crate) concurrent_processing: bool,\n    pub(crate) max_pending_per_key: Option<usize>,\n}\n\nimpl NatsConsumerGroupConfig {\n    pub fn new(range: RangeInclusive<u16>) -> Self;  // panics if start > end\n    pub fn with_prefetch_count(self, v: u16) -> Self;\n    pub fn with_max_retries(self, v: u32) -> Self;\n    pub fn with_handler_timeout(self, v: Duration) -> Self;\n    pub fn with_concurrent_processing(self, v: bool) -> Self;\n    // Accessors: prefetch_count(), min_consumers(), max_consumers(), max_retries(), handler_timeout(), concurrent_processing()\n}\n```\n\nDefaults: `prefetch_count=10`, `max_retries=10`, `handler_timeout=None`, `concurrent_processing=false`.\n\n### 3. NatsConsumerGroupRegistry\n\n```rust\npub struct NatsConsumerGroupRegistry {\n    groups: HashMap<String, NatsConsumerGroup>,\n    client: NatsClient,\n}\n\nimpl NatsConsumerGroupRegistry {\n    pub fn new(client: NatsClient) -> Self;\n    pub async fn register<T, H>(\n        &mut self,\n        config: NatsConsumerGroupConfig,\n        handler_factory: impl Fn() -> H + Send + Sync + 'static,\n    ) -> Result<()>\n    where T: Topic + 'static, H: MessageHandler<T> + Clone + 'static;\n    pub fn start_all(&mut self);\n    pub fn groups(&self) -> &HashMap<String, NatsConsumerGroup>;\n    pub fn groups_mut(&mut self) -> &mut HashMap<String, NatsConsumerGroup>;\n    pub async fn shutdown_all(&mut self);\n}\n```\n\n`register()` declares topology via `NatsTopologyDeclarer`, creates the group with a child token from the client's shutdown token, and inserts into the map. Errors if the group name already exists.\n\n### 4. NatsAutoscalerBackend\n\n```rust\npub trait NatsQueueStatsProvider: Send + Sync {\n    fn get_queue_stats(\n        &self,\n        queue: &str,\n    ) -> impl Future<Output = Result<NatsQueueStats>> + Send;\n}\n\npub struct NatsQueueStats {\n    pub messages_pending: u64,\n    pub messages_ack_pending: u64,\n}\n\npub struct JetStreamStatsProvider {\n    client: NatsClient,\n}\n\nimpl NatsQueueStatsProvider for JetStreamStatsProvider {\n    // Calls client.jetstream().get_stream(queue).get_consumer(\"{queue}-consumer\").info()\n    // Maps info.num_pending → messages_pending, info.num_ack_pending → messages_ack_pending\n}\n```\n\n```rust\npub struct NatsAutoscalerBackend<S: NatsQueueStatsProvider = JetStreamStatsProvider> {\n    stats_provider: S,\n    registry: Arc<Mutex<NatsConsumerGroupRegistry>>,\n}\n\nimpl NatsAutoscalerBackend<JetStreamStatsProvider> {\n    pub fn new(\n        client: NatsClient,\n        registry: Arc<Mutex<NatsConsumerGroupRegistry>>,\n    ) -> Self;\n\n    pub fn autoscaler(\n        client: NatsClient,\n        registry: Arc<Mutex<NatsConsumerGroupRegistry>>,\n        config: AutoscalerConfig,\n    ) -> Autoscaler<Self, Stabilized<ThresholdStrategy>>;\n}\n\nimpl<S: NatsQueueStatsProvider> AutoscalerBackend for NatsAutoscalerBackend<S> {\n    type GroupId = String;\n\n    async fn list_groups(&self) -> Result<Vec<String>>;\n    // Locks registry, returns all group keys\n\n    async fn fetch_metrics(&self, group: &String) -> Result<ScalingMetrics>;\n    // Calls stats_provider.get_queue_stats(queue)\n    // Gets active_consumers and prefetch_count from registry\n    // Returns ScalingMetrics::new(\n    //     stats.messages_pending,\n    //     stats.messages_ack_pending,\n    //     active as u16,\n    //     prefetch,\n    // )\n\n    async fn scale(&self, group: &String, decision: ScalingDecision) -> Result<()>;\n    // Locks registry, calls scale_up() / scale_down() in a loop per magnitude\n}\n```\n\n## File Structure\n\n| File | Action |\n|---|---|\n| `src/backends/nats/consumer_group.rs` | Rewrite — Spawner, scaling, config rework, registry |\n| `src/backends/nats/autoscaler.rs` | New — `NatsAutoscalerBackend`, stats provider |\n| `src/backends/nats/mod.rs` | Add `pub mod autoscaler`, update re-exports |\n| `src/lib.rs` | Add autoscaler re-exports to `nats` module |\n\n## Public API (lib.rs re-exports)\n\n```rust\n#[cfg(feature = \"nats\")]\npub mod nats {\n    pub use crate::backends::nats::{\n        NatsClient, NatsConfig, NatsConsumer,\n        NatsConsumerGroup, NatsConsumerGroupConfig, NatsConsumerGroupRegistry,\n        NatsPublisher, NatsTopologyDeclarer,\n        NatsAutoscalerBackend, NatsQueueStats, NatsQueueStatsProvider,\n        JetStreamStatsProvider,\n    };\n}\n```\n\n## Not In Scope\n\n- FIFO consumer group scaling (sequenced topics) — the current `run_fifo` spawns shard tasks, not individual consumers. Scaling FIFO groups requires a different approach.\n- Custom stats providers beyond JetStream consumer info — the trait exists for testability, but only one implementation ships.\n",
